Package org.openwms.core.configuration.impl.file

Class ApplicationPreference

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openwms.core.configuration.impl.file.AbstractPreference
      • org.openwms.core.configuration.impl.file.GenericPreference
        • org.openwms.core.configuration.impl.file.ApplicationPreference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class ApplicationPreference
extends GenericPreference
implements Serializable
    An ApplicationPreference is used to store a configuration setting in application scope.

    The table model of an ApplicationPreference spans an unique key over the columns C_TYPE and C_KEY.

    It's counterpart in the context of JAXB is the applicationPreference element.

    Author:
    Heiko Scherrer
